    <div class="c2r">
        <h2>A detailed look at schools on the list</h2>
        
        <p>The following data helps better understand each school. </p>
        
        <dl class="examples">
            <dt><img alt="" src="http://dummyimage.com/138" /> ISAT performance by cohort</dt>
            <dd>
                <p>The percent of students meeting or exceeding state standards on standardized tests is tracked for one group, or cohort, of students from 3rd through 8th grade. Tracking a cohort shows how a specific set of students performed over time. </p>
                <p class="mute">Left: <a href="#">Example school</a></p>
            </dd>
            
            <dt><img alt="" src="http://dummyimage.com/138" /> 5Essentials trends</dt>
            <dd>
                <p>An evaluation of a school’s ability to be successful, based on instructional content, school environment, family involvement, teacher collaboration, and effective leadership. The University of Chicago considers these components to be the foundation of a successful school.</p>
                <p class="mute">Left: <a href="#">Example school</a></p>
            </dd>
            
            <dt><img alt="" src="http://dummyimage.com/138" /> Probation status trends</dt>
            <dd>
                <p>Each year CPS evaluates schools to determine if they should be placed on probation and targeted for improvement measures. Schools on probation tend to have more leadership changes, creating a less stable learning environment.</p>
                <p class="mute">Left: <a href="#">Example school</a></p>
            </dd>
            
            <dt><img alt="" src="http://dummyimage.com/138" /> Mobility rate trends</dt>
            <dd>
                <p>Mobility rate measures how many students transfer into, or out of, the school at times other than the beginning or end of a school year. When a school has a high mobility rate, it is more difficult to show school-wide progress.</p>
                <p class="mute">Left: <a href="#">Example school</a></p>
            </dd>
            
            <dt><img alt="" src="http://dummyimage.com/138" /> Enrollment trends</dt>
            <dd>
                <p>The number of students attending the school, taken on the 20th day of each school year. This number is used to determine future needs for space, personnel, equipment, etc.</p>
                <p class="mute">Left: <a href="#">Example school</a></p>
            </dd>
        </dl>
